# Least-privilege reference aclfile for the IronCache console (issue #367).
#
# Load this on every NODE the console talks to, via IRONCACHE_ACLFILE (or the
# `aclfile = "..."` config key). It defines the two scoped users the console
# authenticates AS when it dials a node:
#
#   console_monitor  the read-only POLL loop (health + INFO + best-effort
#                    slowlog/clients panels). Cannot mutate anything and cannot
#                    read a single key value.
#   console_admin    the management surface (CONFIG, CLUSTER ops, ACL admin,
#                    key CRUD, SAVE), but NOT the destructive verbs (FLUSHALL,
#                    FLUSHDB, SHUTDOWN, KEYS, DEBUG, MIGRATE, SWAPDB, ...).
#
# Point the console at one of them with:
#   IRONCACHE_CONSOLE_NODE_USER=console_monitor        (or console_admin)
#   IRONCACHE_CONSOLE_NODE_PASSWORD_FILE=/run/secrets/console_node_password
#
# THIS IS AN EXAMPLE. Before using it:
#   1. Replace both CHANGE_ME_* passwords with real secrets (or feed hashed
#      digests with `#<sha256hex>` instead of `>plaintext`).
#   2. Decide what to do with the `default` user below. It is `off` here so
#      there is NO anonymous access; add your OWN operator/admin user (or set
#      `requirepass` on default) so YOU can still administer the node.
#
# The rule grammar (see docs/design/ACL.md): rules apply left to right,
# last-match-wins. `-@all` then `+cmd` yields "only these commands". `~pattern`
# grants key access (absent = no keys); `&pattern` grants pub/sub channels.

# No anonymous access. Add your own operator user here (e.g.
#   user ops on >YOUR_STRONG_PASSWORD ~* &* +@all
# ) so locking down the console users does not lock YOU out.
user default off

# console_monitor: the read-only poll loop. The console's monitor path issues
# PING, INFO, and (best-effort) SLOWLOG GET + CLIENT LIST; cluster topology is
# fetched over HTTP, never RESP, so no CLUSTER grant is needed. +ping and +info
# are MANDATORY: PING/INFO are not pre-auth-exempt, and a poll that gets NOPERM
# on them marks the node unreachable. +client|list is the read-only CLIENT verb
# for the clients panel. There is deliberately NO `~` key grant, so this user can
# never read a key's value. SLOWLOG is intentionally omitted: it has no
# per-subcommand ACL grant (granting it would mean the whole command, including
# SLOWLOG RESET, which is a mutation), and its argv can name keys; the console's
# slowlog panel is best-effort and simply stays empty for the monitor. The poll
# loop works on +ping +info alone and tolerates NOPERM on the rest.
user console_monitor on >CHANGE_ME_monitor resetkeys resetchannels -@all +ping +info +client|list

# console_admin: scoped management. `+@all -@dangerous` grants every ordinary
# (incl. all data) command and then removes the whole @dangerous class; the
# re-grants below add back exactly the privileged families the console's
# management surface uses. What stays DENIED is the destructive tail of
# @dangerous: FLUSHALL, FLUSHDB, SHUTDOWN, KEYS, SWAPDB, DEBUG, MIGRATE,
# RESTORE, MOVE, SORT, HOTKEYS, PFDEBUG. CLIENT is re-granted only for its READ
# verb (`|list`), so the admin can observe clients but not CLIENT KILL. SLOWLOG
# is re-granted whole (it has no per-subcommand grant), giving the admin SLOWLOG
# GET for the panel plus SLOWLOG RESET, neither of which is data-destructive.
# `~*` enables the key read/write panels; `&*` enables PUBLISH / PUBSUB.
user console_admin on >CHANGE_ME_admin ~* &* +@all -@dangerous +config +cluster +acl +info +save +bgsave +client|list +slowlog
